== do not include this section ==
Obligatory. One file should be in every program: README. It can replace all other files.
If you use automake --gnu or --gnits:

--gnu 
The files INSTALL, NEWS, README, AUTHORS, and ChangeLog, plus one of COPYING.LIB, COPYING.LESSER or COPYING, are 
requiredrequired at the topmost directory of the package. 
--gnits
All of the above.
VERSION is checked to make sure its format complies with Gnits standards.
If VERSION indicates that this is an alpha release, and the file README-alpha appears in the topmost directory of 
package, then it is included in the distribution
The file THANKS is required.

gnu-standards:
The distribution should contain a file named README with a general overview of the package:

the name of the package;
the version number of the package, or refer to where in the package the version can be found;
a general description of what the package does;
a reference to the file INSTALL, which should in turn contain an explanation of the installation procedure;
a brief explanation of any unusual top-level directories or files, or other hints for readers to find their
way around the source;
a reference to the file which contains the copying conditions. The GNU GPL, if used, should be in a file
called COPYING. If the GNU LGPL is used, it should be in a file called COPYING.LESSER.
